# Implementation Plan - Extended Monitor Detection Fix

The goal is to ensure that KeryxPro correctly detects when an extended monitor is plugged in or unplugged, even if the application is already running.

## Proposed Changes

### Logic & Detection

#### [MODIFY] [projection_provider.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/settings/presentation/projection_provider.dart)
- [ ] Modify `ProjectionNotifier` to implement `ScreenRetrieverListener`.
- [ ] In `_init`, register the notifier as a listener via `ScreenRetriever.instance.addListener(this)`.
- [ ] Override `onDisplayAdded` and `onDisplayRemoved` to call `refreshDisplays()`.
- [ ] Override `dispose` to unregister the listener via `ScreenRetriever.instance.removeListener(this)`.

### UI Enhancements

#### [MODIFY] [live_projector_pane.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/live_controller/presentation/widgets/live_projector_pane.dart)
- [ ] In `_Monitor1View`, wrap the status indicator `Row` in a `GestureDetector` or `InkWell` to trigger `refreshDisplays()`.
- [ ] Add a small `IconButton` with `Icons.refresh` next to the "CONNECTED/NOT CONNECTED" text for explicit manual refresh.
- [ ] Add a tooltip to the status area: "Click to refresh monitor status".

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  Launch KeryxPro with only one monitor connected.
2.  Navigate to the **Monitor 1 (Extended)** tab. It should show **NOT CONNECTED**.
3.  Plug in an extended monitor.
4.  Verify that the status automatically changes to **CONNECTED** (via the listener).
5.  Unplug the monitor and verify it changes back to **NOT CONNECTED**.
6.  Manually click the refresh icon and verify it correctly updates the state.
